<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870608-0132 </DOCNO><HL> Royal Trustco to Buy Assets</HL><DD> 06/08/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> RYL.A T.SETENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)PETROLEUM (PET)NATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG) </IN><DATELINE> TORONTO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Royal Trustco Ltd. said its Royal Trust Energy Corp. unit agreed to purchase certain oil and gas properties in western Canada from Sherritt Gordon Mines Ltd. for 25 million Canadian dollars ($18.6 million).    Sherritt Gordon, a mining and fertilizer concern, said the transaction doesn't include natural gas reserves recently acquired from Unocal Corp.'s Canadian unit. Sherritt previously said it was considering the sale of its other oil and gas assets.    Royal Trustco, Canada's second-largest trust concern, said the properties are being acquired on behalf of several of its funds and other affiliated companies. </TEXT></DOC>